						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Sik wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Random thought: what would happen if it focused first on sprites and later on backgrounds? (at least having sprites alone you can make some minimal games, but having backgrounds alone will limit your choices more)</div><br />What kind of game could be made with only sprites? You'd probably need a background to 1. define where the sprites are allowed to go (such as top and bottom walls in Pong) and 2. display the score. Even if you could do so with only sprites, I conjecture that doing so with a background would be easier to understand.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">dougeff wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Will there be a primer on ASM language, or will this be explained as you go?</div><br />Both. The installation chapter will link to the <a href="http://6502.org/tutorials/" class="postlink">list of 6502 tutorials</a> if the user wants to learn assembly language in another environment first. But each instruction and each addressing mode will be explained as it's first used. This is why I've broken &quot;Hello World&quot; down the way I did.</div>

